{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Making a M√∂bius cake","content":"<p><em>This is a guest post by <a href=\"http://twitter.com/ponywithhiccups\" target=\"_blank\">@ponywithhiccups</a>, a cool gal who sometimes makes epic nerdy cakes.</em></p>\n<p>It was a simple deal: Swizec would make a cake for me and I would make a cake for him. After many many not so subtle hints I got <a title=\"A technical post about cake\" href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/a-technical-post-about-cake/swizec/2626\">exactly what I wanted</a>.</p>\n<p>He wanted this in a cake form &#8211;&gt;</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2739\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/making-a-mobius-cake/ponywithhiccups/2737/moebiusgeara\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-2739\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2739\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/MoebiusGearA-300x226.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"226\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/MoebiusGearA-300x226.jpg 300w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/MoebiusGearA.jpeg 478w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">this: a m√∂bius gear</p></div>\n<p>Ignoring the gears I was eager to make the complicated cake, how hard could it be?</p>\n<p>I&#8217;ve heard of m√∂bius architecture so it wasn&#8217;t like I was the first person making a 3D mobius strip able to stand on its own. A quick google search and there it was: a nice picture of a 3D model. Yay, I could actually do this!</p>\n<div style=\"width: 386px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/twisted_33.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"376\" height=\"435\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">M√∂bius arhitecture</p></div>\n<p>It looked simple enough at first, just cut a hole in cake dough, then cut it in half and bend it a little &#8211; voila done! But then I started thinking and soon realised you can&#8217;t just bend a cake. The cake dough is not a bendy material; it is actually very brittle and sensitive and not cooperative at all! And what would happen tho the fill if the layers were vertical and not horizontal and how the heck do you cut a cake like that? Nope, the layers have to be horizontal. And there was my first big problem &#8211; the cake layers were not simple shapes anymore.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2783\" style=\"width: 624px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/MOBIUS-CAKE_00031.jpg\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-2783 \" title=\"MOBIUS CAKE_0003\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/MOBIUS-CAKE_00031-1024x878.jpg\" alt=\"first sketch\" width=\"614\" height=\"527\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/MOBIUS-CAKE_00031-1024x878.jpg 1024w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/MOBIUS-CAKE_00031-300x257.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">First sketch</p></div>\n<h2>3D modeling to the rescue!</h2>\n<p>Just looking at the pretty picture of m√∂bius arhitecture didn&#8217;t tell me how to cut. I had to figure that bit out on my own. Since I&#8217;m too lazy to do things by hand I did it on a computer.</p>\n<p>After some trial and error and a lot of clumsy modeling things started making sense. It turns out a 3D m√∂bius structure is just two m√∂bius strips intertwined or a square making half a rotation along a circular path.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2755\" style=\"width: 558px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/cad2.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2755 \" title=\"cad2\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/cad2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"548\" height=\"438\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/cad2.jpg 914w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/cad2-300x239.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 548px) 100vw, 548px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">One of the two strips making the cake</p></div>\n<div id=\"attachment_2756\" style=\"width: 555px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/cad1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2756 \" title=\"cad1\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/cad1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"545\" height=\"440\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/cad1.jpg 909w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/cad1-300x242.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 545px) 100vw, 545px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Rotated squares</p></div>\n<div id=\"attachment_2757\" style=\"width: 522px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/fatty.jpeg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2757 \" title=\"fatty\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/fatty.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"512\" height=\"384\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/fatty.jpeg 640w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/fatty-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">A fat cake</p></div>\n<p>All I needed to do now was to cut the virtual cake in layers.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2758\" style=\"width: 522px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/cuts4.jpeg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2758 \" title=\"cuts4\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/cuts4.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"512\" height=\"384\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/cuts4.jpeg 640w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/cuts4-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">And the layers look weiiiiird ... like deformed toilet seats</p></div>\n<p>Now that I knew what the layers would look like all I could think was <em>&#8220;I wish I could <a href=\"http://www.neatorama.com/2011/07/20/mobius-cake/\" target=\"_blank\">3d print cake</a>!&#8221;</em></p>\n<h2>The cakeday</h2>\n<p>I was making a yummy chocolate cake with sour cherries in the middle! So even if it turned out horribly deformed it would still be tasty, just look at the ingredients!</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2761\" style=\"width: 458px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-12-43-18-131.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2761 \" title=\"2011-10-28-12-43-18-131\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-12-43-18-131.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"448\" height=\"336\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-12-43-18-131.jpg 640w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-12-43-18-131-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 448px) 100vw, 448px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">The tasty ingredients</p></div>\n<p>It all started pretty normal: heating, mixing, cooling, etc. and then came the time to cut the bisquit, the moment I did not look forward to. With the help of a ruler, a compass and colorful pencils I soon had a cutting template.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2762\" style=\"width: 548px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/IMG719.jpg\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-2762 \" title=\"IMG719\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/IMG719-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"538\" height=\"717\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/IMG719-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/IMG719-225x300.jpg 225w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/IMG719.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 538px) 100vw, 538px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">This is not normal, but on math it is</p></div>\n<p>And there I was: a sharp knife in my right and a paper template in my left, ready to make a mess.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2765\" style=\"width: 624px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/IMG718.jpg\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-2765 \" title=\"IMG718\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/IMG718-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"614\" height=\"461\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/IMG718-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/IMG718-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">That was easy!</p></div>\n<p>And it got messy fast, the bisquit is very crumbly. Not my favourite material at all!</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2766\" style=\"width: 346px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-16-49-43-336.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2766 \" title=\"2011-10-28-16-49-43-336\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-16-49-43-336.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"336\" height=\"448\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-16-49-43-336.jpg 480w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-16-49-43-336-225x300.jpg 225w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 336px) 100vw, 336px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">First layer</p></div>\n<p>It was during the process of cutting the first layer when I had the what-the-hell-am-i-even-doing moment. The first layer looked like a giant crooked eye and it almost fell apart when i moved it. And it wasn&#8217;t getting any better.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2767\" style=\"width: 346px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-17-08-44-674.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2767 \" title=\"2011-10-28-17-08-44-674\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-17-08-44-674.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"336\" height=\"448\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-17-08-44-674.jpg 480w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-17-08-44-674-225x300.jpg 225w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 336px) 100vw, 336px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Am I making a giant nut cake?</p></div>\n<div id=\"attachment_2768\" style=\"width: 394px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-17-53-59-968.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2768 \" title=\"2011-10-28-17-53-59-968\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-17-53-59-968.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"384\" height=\"288\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-17-53-59-968.jpg 640w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/2011-10-28-17-53-59-968-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 384px) 100vw, 384px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Nearly gave up at this stage</p></div>\n<p>The chocolate fill was almost liquid, the cherries decided it was time to run away, the cake did not look like a mobius cake at all! I opened the windows to make the whole kitchen a giant cooler and hoped for the best.</p>\n<p>Then I just kept adding a metric fuckton of chocolate.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2769\" style=\"width: 624px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/IMG725.jpg\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-2769 \" title=\"IMG725\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/IMG725-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"614\" height=\"461\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/IMG725-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/IMG725-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">I did it!</p></div>\n<p>And i did it!</p>\n<p>It was not pretty, it was not elegant, not even slightly symetric, but it was a m√∂bius cake!</p>\n<p>And I still had a lot of leftover material, so I made a tiny surprise gear cake üòâ</p>\n<div style=\"width: 510px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img title=\"It's not a mobius gear cake, but a mobius + gear cake\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/tumblr_ltsgrvEsBK1qekjngo1_5002.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">It&#39;s not a m√∂bius gear cake, but a mobius + gear cake</p></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Note from Swizec: It was fucking delicious!</em></p>\n<h6 class=\"zemanta-related-title\" style=\"font-size: 1em;\">Related articles</h6>\n<ul class=\"zemanta-article-ul\">\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://www.neatorama.com/2011/07/20/mobius-cake/\">M√∂bius Cake</a> (neatorama.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://cathweber.blogspot.com/2011/10/epic-cake-disaster.html\">an epic cake disaster</a> (cathweber.blogspot.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://www.core77.com/blog/videos/mobius_a_stop-motion_sculpture_by_eness_20194.asp\">&#8220;MOBIUS,&#8221; a Stop-Motion Sculpture by ENESS</a> (core77.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://letsplaymath.net/2011/09/21/moebius-noodles-photo-game/\">Moebius Noodles Photo Game</a> (letsplaymath.net)</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; height: 15px;\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none; float: right;\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=1995dbbb-ce88-41c7-9ca3-7c3aa9fdeeb4\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" /></a></div>\n"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Swizec Blog","subtitle":"Fetch Data From Local WP Install"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"a0515acb-438b-52c4-ba34-987dd35c7d99"}}